cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.DC, cs.AR, cs.SE

This paper is about optimizing deep learning primitives, specifically convolutions, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.AR (Hardware Architecture). Finally, the paper discusses the development of a hybrid solution, which could be relevant to cs.SE (Software Engineering).
